				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$t_{0}$$\end{document} residual distribution. Finally, the asymmetric nature of the space charge distortions at the cathode causes a double-peak structure for cathode-stitched tracks, depending on whether the particle crossed the cathode from positive to negative x or vice versa.Fig. 13
