The top figures show the reconstruction and identification efficiency for the triggered test-beam particles as a function of the number of 2D hits they produce in the detector (including hits produced by their interaction and decay products). The efficiencies for the full simulation both increase as a function of the number of hits and eventually plateau at ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
