				\begin{document}$$\mu ^+$$\end{document}) and momentum setting combinations (1, 2, 3, 6 and 7 GeV/c). It was also shown that the main cause of these inefficiencies arises from background contamination from both cosmic and beam-halo sources. In background-removed simulation samples the triggered test-beam particle reconstruction and identification efficiency above a few hundred hits is almost 100% in all cases. A comparison of data and MC shows agreement within 5% for the reconstruction and identification efficiency for different triggered beam-particle species across the beam momentum values, and possible sources for the small observed efficiency differences were discussed.

